{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01FYyMqZcqxwfdKSwwTAt2LA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I understand the vulnerability now. In `CamelCoapResource.handleRequest`, untrusted CoAP URI query parameters are blindly used as Camel message header names (lines 102-110). A remote client can therefore inject or overwrite internal Camel control headers (the `Camel*`-prefixed reserved headers, such as the `CamelCoap*` headers this very method reads back to build the response), modifying object attributes that control downstream processing — CWE-915.\n\nThe idiomatic Camel remediation is to apply a `HeaderFilterStrategy` that drops reserved `Camel`-prefixed names when copying external headers into the exchange, exactly as the HTTP-based consumers do. Let me apply it."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1522,"cache_read_input_tokens":47264,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1522},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"abea2b38-393a-4a0f-8f91-eb843fd2a806","uuid":"a7fde8c4-cfe7-40a3-80e6-5a16e9bdde26","request_id":"req_011Cca1bm1SWNBkSJJq31Q2N"}
