{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01JE6BWzVt5Q8ymmGnf2ZoZs","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The fix is complete. The `camel-support` dependency is declared in the module's POM, so both `org.apache.camel.spi.HeaderFilterStrategy` and `org.apache.camel.support.DefaultHeaderFilterStrategy` resolve.\n\n## Summary\n\n**Vulnerability (CWE-915 – Object Attribute Modification):** In `CamelCoapResource.handleRequest`, the incoming CoAP request's URI query parameters were used verbatim as Camel message header *names*:\n\n```java\ncamelExchange.getIn().setHeader(s.substring(0, i), s.substring(i + 1));\n```\n\nA remote client could supply query parameters named with Camel's reserved `Camel*` prefix (e.g. `CamelCoapResponseCode`, `CamelCoapMaxAge`, `CamelCoapETag`, or any other internal control header) to inject or overwrite internal exchange attributes that drive downstream routing and the response — including headers this very method reads back when building the CoAP response.\n\n**Remediation:** I applied the same `HeaderFilterStrategy` pattern that Camel's HTTP-based consumers use. A `DefaultHeaderFilterStrategy` configured with `CAMEL_FILTER_STARTS_WITH` (\"Camel\"/\"camel\", case-insensitive) is consulted via `applyFilterToExternalHeaders(...)` before each query parameter is set. Reserved Camel-internal header names are now skipped, while legitimate application query parameters still pass through unchanged — so intended behavior is preserved.\n\nChanges are confined to `components/camel-coap/src/main/java/org/apache/camel/coap/CamelCoapResource.java` (two new imports, a static filter-strategy field + factory method, and the guarded query-parameter loop). No commits, pushes, or other repository operations were performed."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":545,"cache_read_input_tokens":52957,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":545},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"abea2b38-393a-4a0f-8f91-eb843fd2a806","uuid":"996880a7-63e2-4703-bf62-0d709674c9da","request_id":"req_011Cca1eYpYPXmpNiv8rUsvu"}
